headline: Micron and 28 Other S&P 500 Stocks Hit 52-Week Highs on Wednesday. These 12 Are Doing It Again Today.
summary: The stock has gained 241% in 2025, making it one of 2025’s big winners as investors finally realized that AI requires huge amounts of its memory chips.  Its stock was up 1.7%, at $291.67 in premarket trading on Friday as investors looked set to press those bets heading into the end of the year, but was off 0.4% in morning trading.  Lam Research, however, was up 1.1% at $179.28, making it the group’s top gainer.

headline: These Stocks Are Moving the Most Today: Nvidia, Micron, Nike, Tesla, Lam Research, Coupang, Newmont, and More
summary: Nvidia is rising after reaching an agreement with AI start-up Groq, while Lam Research stock is on track for a record high.

headline: S&P Futures Muted in Thin Post-Christmas Trade
summary: March S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESH26) are trending down -0.03% this morning as trading resumed after the Christmas holiday, with activity subdued and volumes expected to remain light ahead of a shortened New Year’s week.
